r-the-anger-are-working-hard-to-14540181.php | archive-date=2019-10-22 | url-status=live | quote=We did see damage to our system because of the wind. When we patrolled all 25,000 miles of lines that we turned off, we found more than 100 confirmed cases of wind-related damage \u2014 including trees into power lines and downed power lines. Had we not shut off power, this type of damage could have sparked a fire. In fact, vegetation contacting lines was the very cause of a number of fires in the North Bay two years ago. }} </ref>\n\n}}\n\n[[Category:2019 in California]]\n[[Category:October 2019 events in the United States]]\n[[Category:Pacific Gas and Electric Company]]\n[[Category:Power outages in the United States]]\n", "name_user": "Muboshgu", "label": "safe", "comment": "date formats perMOS:DATEFORMATbyscript", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2019_California_power_shutoffs"}
